More TSMC Fabs in the U.S.
--------------------------

From the Wall Street Journal ( https://www.wsj.com/tech/trump-chip-maker-ts=
mc-expected-to-announce-100-billion-investment-in-u-s-02a44399 ) :

Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Co. plans to invest at least $100 billio=
n more in chip-manufacturing plants in the U.S. over the next several years=
 under a plan announced Monday by the company and President Trump. TSMC pla=
ns to use the funds to add to its chip manufacturing in Arizona. It will co=
nstruct three new chip plants, two chip-packaging plants and a research and=
 development center, Chief Executive C.C. Wei said during a White House app=
earance with the president. Such an expansion would advance a long-pursued =
U.S. goal to revive the domestic semiconductor industry after manufacturing=
 fled largely to Asian countries in recent decades.

Trump called building up the industry a matter of economic and national sec=
urity, as well as evidence that his tariff threats were working. =E2=80=9CI=
f they did [the chips] in Taiwan to send them here they=E2=80=99ll have 25%=
 or $30% or 50% or whatever the number may be=E2=80=9D in tariffs, Trump sa=
id. =E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99ll go only up. By doing it here, there=E2=80=99s no=
 tariffs.=E2=80=9D

TSMC, the world=E2=80=99s largest contract chip maker, set down roots in Ar=
izona in 2020, when it said it would build a chip factory there for $12 bil=
lion. Its ambitions for the site have expanded rapidly since, with two more=
 factories and a total investment of $65 billion. The company=E2=80=99s fir=
st factory began mass production late last year. With the new investments, =
the company is planning to spend a total of $165 billion on its U.S. factor=
ies.

The most interesting part of this announcement is arguably the non-fab port=
ion: TSMC is building two packaging plants and a research and development c=
enter, in addition to the three new fabs. Packaging plants have been a big =
focus of the U.S. going back even to the original TSMC announcement of its =
first Arizona fab in President Trump's first term; they are an essential pa=
rt of making a chip into a useful microprocessor. Packaging, however, has t=
raditionally been very labor intensive; it's the part of semiconductor manu=
facturing that I discussed in the opening of last November's A Chance to Bu=
ild ( https://stratechery.com/2024/a-chance-to-build/?access_token=3DeyJhbG=
ciOiJSUzI1NiIsImtpZCI6InN0cmF0ZWNoZXJ5LnBhc3Nwb3J0Lm9ubGluZSIsInR5cCI6IkpXV=
